
[1]arrow-root

   AR'ROW-ROOT, n.

   1. The Maranta; a genus of plants, natives of the Indies. The Indians
   are said to employ the roots of the arundinacea, in extracting the
   virus of poisoned arrows; whence the name. There are several species.
   From the root of the arundinacea, or starch-plant, is obtained the
   arrow-root of the shops.

   2. The starch of the maranta, or arrow-root, a nutritive medicinal
   food.
